Field Documentation

int osd_object::oo_compat_dot_created

Following two members are used to indicate the presence of dot and dotdot in the given directory.

This is required for interop mode (b11826).

struct inode* osd_object::oo_inode [read]

Inode for file system object represented by this osd_object.

This inode is pinned for the whole duration of lu_object life.

Not modified concurrently (either setup early during object creation, or assigned by osd_object_create() under write lock).
